projects.pqueue.priorityqueues

Class LinearPriorityQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.pqueue.priorityqueues.LinearPriorityQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type held by the container.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, PriorityQueue<T>

    public class LinearPriorityQueue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PriorityQueue<T>

    LinearPriorityQueue is a priority queue implemented as a linear Collection of common FIFOQueues, where the FIFOQueues themselves hold objects with the same priority (in the order they were inserted).

    You must implement the methods in this file! To receive any credit for the unit tests related to this class, your implementation must use whichever linear Collection you want (e.g ArrayList, LinkedList, Queue), or even the various List and FIFOQueue implementations that we provide for you. It is also possible to use raw arrays.
